# Scenario: Catalog is advertised over plain HTTP. Agent MUST refuse.
# Expected outcome: agent does NOT fetch the catalog and reports the violation.

### Request hits a plain-HTTP origin
GET http://example.com/some/page HTTP/1.1
Accept: text/html

### Response includes a catalog Link header
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/html
Link: <http://example.com/agent-catalog.json>; rel="agent-catalog"

<html>...</html>

### Agent MUST NOT make this request
# (no further requests; the agent reports "agent-catalog advertised over plain HTTP, refused")
